Time flows upward.  Releases happen when all actions
below them are completed.

This document is at risk of radical change whenever I
feel like it.

- means to do
+ means done

--------------------------------------------

Release 2.0 (blue sky)

- Think about ports to wxWindows, Python, ...

Release 1.0 (the destination)

- Get it all right
- Integration with e.g. tv card software 
	- developed and maintained by a leutenant (i.e. not me)
	- Needs ability to start/stop viewing and recording
	- Might use JNI?
- Internationalisation
- Printing
	- Keep the browser option for maximum compatibility
	- Add save html option
	- Support tv_to_latex tool, viewing and printing (what about windows?)
	- How to print on Windows?
	- Use Java's printing capabilities?
- Use JNI for grabber etc?
- Facilitate community devt of default settings in each situation (how?)
- FAQ?
- Other platforms - investigate Mac, BSD, others

